                    <span>I'm pleased to have authored one of the chapters in this edited volume (Chapter Five, "Reel Life: The Social Geometry of Reality Shows"). The company it appears in is an impressive array of disciplines and perspectives brought to bear on a fascinating turn in broadcast television production. The articles range from insightful to inciteful, and address more than a dozen aspects of shows ranging from Survivor to Fear Factor.</span>
                  
              
